    "alias": "CVE-2007-3722",
    "description": "The 4BSD process scheduler in the FreeBSD kernel performs scheduling based on CPU billing gathered from periodic process sampling ticks, which allows local users to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) by performing voluntary nanosecond sleeps that result in the process not being active during a clock interrupt, as described in \"Secretly Monopolizing the CPU Without Superuser Privileges.\"",
    "id": "GSD-2007-3722"
